HEADWORD: Mucigenous
<hw>Mu*cig"e*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Connected with the formation of mucin; resembling mucin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>mucigenous</qex> basis is manufactured at the expense of
the ordinary protoplasm of the cell.</q> <rj><qau>Foster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mucilage</ent>⟦br⟧
